wsdl:portType.name: ReportService
wsdl:portType.wsdl:documentation: <summary> The Report service interface contains functionality to retreive Statistics and Reports for a webcast. - Statistics contains datetime based data - Reports contains datetime independent data for a webcast, module or visitor All methods return an enum value to indicate error or success. See <see cref="T:ReturnCode" /> for the possible values. </summary>

wsdl:operation.name: WebcastGet
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Get a <see cref="T:Webcast" /> containing running totals of minutes watched and amount of viewers for a specified period of time </summary> <param name="Webcast">A <see cref="T:Webcast" />, or null if not found</param> <param name="Username">Username used for authentication</param> <param name="Password">Password used for authentication</param> <param name="WebcastCode">Webcast Code, consisting of CustomerName/YYYYMMDD_serialnumber</param> <param name="Start">Specifies a starting point for gathering running totals</param> <param name="Period">Used for calculating an end point for gathering running totals. This period is added to <see cref="P:Start" /></param> <param name="Filter">Use WebcastFilter to retrieve only specific report data (such as poll)</param> <returns>a <see cref="T:ReturnCode" />, returns either <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ClientNotAuthorizedOrUnkown" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.Success" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.NoData" /> or <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ServerError" /> when an exception occurs</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: WebcastCurrentViewersGet
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Get a count of the current amount of viewers of a specific webcast, this result can be cached for 1 minute. </summary> <param name="ViewersCount">The number of viewers</param> <param name="Username">Username used for authentication</param> <param name="Password">Password used for authentication</param> <param name="WebcastCode">Webcast Code</param> <returns>a <see cref="T:ReturnCode" />, returns either <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ClientNotAuthorizedOrUnkown" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.Success" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.NoData" /> or <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ServerError" /> when an exception occurs</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: WebcastSummaryGet
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Get a <see cref="T:WebcastSummary" />, this data can be cached for 1 minute. </summary> <param name="WebcastSummary">A <see cref="T:WebcastSummary" />, or null if not found</param> <param name="Username">Username used for authentication</param> <param name="Password">Password used for authentication</param> <param name="WebcastCode">Webcast Code, consisting of CustomerName/YYYYMMDD_serialnumber</param> <returns>a <see cref="T:ReturnCode" />, returns either <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ClientNotAuthorizedOrUnkown" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.Success" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.NoData" /> or <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ServerError" /> when an exception occurs</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: CustomerGet
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Get a <see cref="T:Customer" />, containing running totals of visitors and views </summary> <param name="Customer">a <see cref="T:Customer" />, or null if not found</param> <param name="Username">Username used for authentication</param> <param name="Password">Password used for authentication</param> <param name="CustomerCode">Code used to identify a customer</param> <param name="Start">Specifies a starting point for gathering running totals</param> <param name="Period">Used for calculating an end point for gathering running totals. This period is added to <see cref="P:Start" /></param> <returns>a <see cref="T:ReturnCode" />, returns either <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ClientNotAuthorizedOrUnkown" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.Success" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.NoData" /> or <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ServerError" /> when an exception occurs</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: ChartGet
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Get a <see cref="T:ChartList" />, a collection of <see cref="T:Chart" />s, which itself is a collection of <see cref="T:ChartItem" />s </summary> <param name="Charts">A <see cref="T:ChartList" /></param> <param name="Username">Username used for authentication</param> <param name="Password">Password used for authentication</param> <param name="ObjectType"><see cref="T:ObjectType" /> for a list of possible values</param> <param name="ObjectIdentifier">CustomerCode for <see cref="P:ObjectType" /> Customer, <see cref="T:WebcastKey" /> for Webcast, <see cref="T:System.Guid" /> for Form</param> <param name="Start">Specifies a starting point for gathering timed information</param> <param name="Period">Used for calculating an end point for gathering timed information. This period is added to <see cref="P:Start" /></param> <param name="ChartTypes">A comma delimeted list of chart type names from <see cref="T:Webservice.Charts" />, where "Chart" will be appended to the type name</param> <param name="PageSize">Used for paginating Chart results</param> <param name="PageNumber">Used for paginating Chart results</param> <returns>a <see cref="T:ReturnCode" /> <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ClientNotAuthorizedOrUnkown" /> when authentication or authorisation fails <see cref="F:ReturnCode.InvalidInput" /> when <see cref="P:ObjectType" /> does not conform to validation <see cref="F:ReturnCode.InvalidChartForObject" /> when <see cref="P:ChartTypes" /> can not be converted to <see cref="T:IChart" /> <see cref="F:ReturnCode.InvalidInput" /> when <see cref="P:ObjectType" /> is unexpected </returns>

wsdl:operation.name: VisitorSearch
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Search Visitors by (part of) email address returns a VisitorSummary, for detailed visitor info see: <see cref="M:VisitorGet()" /> </summary> <param name="VisitorSummaries">a collection of <see cref="T:VisitorSummary" /></param> <param name="Username">Username used for authentication</param> <param name="Password">Password used for authentication</param> <param name="WebcastCode">Webcast Code, consisting of CustomerName/YYYYMMDD_serialnumber</param> <param name="Email">(part of) an emailadress used for searching</param> <param name="Start">Specifies a starting point for gathering timed information</param> <param name="Period">Used for calculating an end point for gathering timed information. This period is added to <see cref="P:Start" /></param> <param name="PageSize">Used for paginating results</param> <param name="PageNumber">Used for paginating results</param> <param name="Ordering">Used to order results</param> <returns>a <see cref="T:ReturnCode" />, returns either <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ClientNotAuthorizedOrUnkown" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.Success" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.NoData" /> or <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ServerError" /> when an exception occurs</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: VisitorGet
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Get a <see cref="T:Visitor" />, containing detailed reports about visitors </summary> <param name="Visitor">A <see cref="T:Visitor" />, or null if not found</param> <param name="Username">Username used for authentication</param> <param name="Password">Password used for authentication</param> <param name="WebcastCode">Webcast Code, consisting of CustomerName/YYYYMMDD_serialnumber</param> <param name="VisitorId">Uniquely identifies a <see cref="T:Visitor" /></param> <param name="Start">Specifies a starting point for gathering timed information</param> <param name="Period">Used for calculating an end point for gathering timed information. This period is added to <see cref="P:Start" /></param> <returns>a <see cref="T:ReturnCode" />, returns either <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ClientNotAuthorizedOrUnkown" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.Success" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.NoData" /> or <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ServerError" /> when an exception occurs</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: FormsGet
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Get a collection of <see cref="T:Forms" /> </summary> <param name="Forms">A collection of <see cref="T:Forms" /></param> <param name="UserName">Username used for authentication</param> <param name="Password">Password used for authentication</param> <param name="WebcastCode">Webcast Code, consisting of CustomerName/YYYYMMDD_serialnumber</param> <returns>a <see cref="T:ReturnCode" />, returns either <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ClientNotAuthorizedOrUnkown" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.Success" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.NoData" /> or <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ServerError" /> when an exception occurs</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: ExcelSend
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Request for an Excel report of a specific webcast to be sent to <see cref="P:Email" /> </summary> <param name="Username">Username used for authentication</param> <param name="Password">Password used for authentication</param> <param name="WebcastCode">Webcast Code, consisting of CustomerName/YYYYMMDD_serialnumber</param> <param name="Email">a valid email address</param> <returns>a <see cref="T:ReturnCode" />, returns either <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ClientNotAuthorizedOrUnkown" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.Success" /> or <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ServerError" /> when an exception occurs</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: SendRegistrantExcel
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Request for an Excel report of a specific webcast to be sent to <see cref="P:Email" /> </summary> <param name="Username">Username used for authentication</param> <param name="Password">Password used for authentication</param> <param name="WebcastCode">Webcast Code, consisting of CustomerName/YYYYMMDD_serialnumber</param> <param name="Email">a valid email address</param> <returns>a <see cref="T:ReturnCode" />, returns either <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ClientNotAuthorizedOrUnkown" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.Success" /> or <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ServerError" /> when an exception occurs</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: UsersExcelSend
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Request for an Excel report of users from a specific client to be sent to <see cref="P:Email" /> </summary> <param name="Username">Username used for authentication</param> <param name="Password">Password used for authentication</param> <param name="CustomerCode">Code used to identify a customer</param> <param name="Email">a valid email address</param> <returns>a <see cref="T:ReturnCode" />, returns either <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ClientNotAuthorizedOrUnkown" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.Success" /> or <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ServerError" /> when an exception occurs</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: VisitorCompletedForm
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Tests if a certain form has been completed by a specific visitor </summary> <param name="Answered">true if answered</param> <param name="Username">Username used for authentication</param> <param name="Password">Password used for authentication</param> <param name="WebcastCode">Webcast Code, consisting of CustomerName/YYYYMMDD_serialnumber</param> <param name="VisitorId">Uniquely identifies a <see cref="T:Visitor" /></param> <param name="FormId">Uniquely identifies a <see cref="T:Form" /></param> <returns>a <see cref="T:ReturnCode" />, returns either <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ClientNotAuthorizedOrUnkown" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.Success" /> or <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ServerError" /> when an exception occurs</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: UserGet
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Get a <see cref="T:User" />, containing webcast usage statistics </summary> <param name="User">A <see cref="T:User" /></param> <param name="Username">Username used for authentication</param> <param name="Password">Password used for authentication</param> <param name="CustomerUserName">Uniquely identies a <see cref="T:User" /></param> <returns>a <see cref="T:ReturnCode" />, returns either <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ClientNotAuthorizedOrUnkown" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.Success" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.NoData" /> or <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ServerError" /> when an exception occurs</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: WebcastSearch
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Get a collection of <see cref="T:WebcastSummary" />s </summary> <param name="WebcastSummaries">a collection of <see cref="T:WebcastSummary" />s, or null if not found</param> <param name="Username">Username used for authentication</param> <param name="Password">Password used for authentication</param> <param name="CustomerCode">Code used to identify a customer</param> <param name="Title">(part of) a webcast title</param> <param name="Tags">a collection of <see cref="T:Tags" /></param> <param name="PageSize">Used for paginating results</param> <param name="PageNumber">Used for paginating results</param> <param name="Order">Orders the results</param> <returns>a <see cref="T:ReturnCode" />, returns either <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ClientNotAuthorizedOrUnkown" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.Success" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.NoData" /> or <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ServerError" /> when an exception occurs</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: UserSearch
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Get a list of <see cref="T:UserSummary" />s based on the specified filters. </summary> <param name="UserSummaries">a list of <see cref="T:UserSummary" />s</param> <param name="Username">Username used for authentication</param> <param name="Password">Password used for authentication</param> <param name="CustomerCode">Code used to identify a customer, returns <see cref="F:ReturnCode.InvalidInput" /> when not a null or empty</param> <param name="UserNameFilter">(part of) the user's name</param> <param name="UserUsernameFilter">(part of) the user's username</param> <param name="UserEmailFilter">(part of) a valid emailaddress</param> <param name="UserTagsFilter">a collection of <see cref="T:Tags" /></param> <param name="PageSize">Used for paginating results</param> <param name="PageNumber">Used for paginating results</param> <param name="Order">Orders the results</param> <returns>a <see cref="T:ReturnCode" />, returns either <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ClientNotAuthorizedOrUnkown" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.InvalidInput" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.Success" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.NoData" /> or <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ServerError" /> when an exception occurs</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: UserCount
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Get a count of <see cref="T:User" />s based on the specified filters. </summary> <param name="Count">The count of <see cref="T:User" />s</param> <param name="Username">Username used for authentication</param> <param name="Password">Password used for authentication</param> <param name="CustomerCode">Code used to identify a customer, returns <see cref="F:ReturnCode.InvalidInput" /> when not a null or empty</param> <param name="UserNameFilter">(part of) the user's name</param> <param name="UserUsernameFilter">(part of) the user's username</param> <param name="UserEmailFilter">(part of) a valid emailaddress</param> <param name="UserTagsFilter">a collection of <see cref="T:Tags" /></param> <returns>a <see cref="T:ReturnCode" />, returns either <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ClientNotAuthorizedOrUnkown" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.InvalidInput" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.Success" />, <see cref="F:ReturnCode.NoData" /> or <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ServerError" /> when an exception occurs</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: VisitorWatchedSince
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Gets an array of <see cref="T:System.DateTime" />s, from a specific starting point </summary> <param name="Watched">An array of <see cref="T:System.DateTime" /></param> <param name="Username">Username used for authentication</param> <param name="Password">Password used for authentication</param> <param name="WebcastCode">Webcast Code, consisting of CustomerName/YYYYMMDD_serialnumber</param> <param name="VisitorId">Uniquely identifies a <see cref="T:Visitor" /></param> <param name="From">Specifies a starting point for gathering timed information</param> <returns>a <see cref="T:ReturnCode" />, returns either <see cref="F:ReturnCode.Success" /> or <see cref="F:ReturnCode.ServerError" /> when an exception occurs</returns>
